ical methods for addressing them. It considers the process of de-institutionalisation in its entire complexity.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><object class=\"wp-block-file__embed\" data=\"https:\/\/www.hopeandhomes.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Deinstitutionalising-and-Transforming-Childrens-Services.pdf\" type=\"application\/pdf\" style=\"width:100%;height:600px\" aria-label=\"Embed of Deinstitutionalising-and-Transforming-Childrens-Services.\"><\/object><a id=\"wp-block-file--media-32043261-1050-4644-bbde-8a300fe19d32\" href=\"https:\/\/www.hopeandhomes.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Deinstitutionalising-and-Transforming-Childrens-Services.pdf\">Deinstitutionalising-and-Transforming-Childrens-Services<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.hopeandhomes.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Deinstitutionalising-and-Transforming-Childrens-Services.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button\" download aria-describedby=\"wp-block-file--media-32043261-1050-4644-bbde-8a300fe19d32\">Download<\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The purpose of this document is to assist policy makers, practitioners and other concerned individuals to transform systems of institutional care into those based on family and community support.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n","protected":false},"featured_media":2901,"template":"","tags":[25,51,80,66],"acf":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v19.2 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>A Good Practice Guide: Deinstitutionalising and Transforming Children&#039;s Services - Hope and Homes<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"The purpose of this document is to assist policy makers to transform systems of institutional care into those based on family.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.hopeandhomes.org\/publications\/d